Attribution
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

OVERTURE is an unofficial, fan-made tool for the game OpenDominion. It is not
affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by the OpenDominion project or its
maintainers.

OpenDominion — https://github.com/OpenDominion/OpenDominion — is licensed under
the GNU Affero General Public License v3. OVERTURE derives from it in two ways,
and inherits its license accordingly:

  * The engine is a clean-room reimplementation of OpenDominion's round-50
    game rules (production, population, combat, defense, and the per-tick
    economy). The Rust source documents the upstream PHP calculators it mirrors.

  * The game data in `data/` (race, tech, spell, and round tables) is mirrored
    bit-for-bit from OpenDominion's round-50 source so the simulation matches
    the live game exactly.

All OpenDominion game content, names, and rules remain the property of the
OpenDominion project and its contributors.

